18 (4) "Solvolysis" means a manufacturing process in which post-
19 use polymers are purified with the aid of solvents, while heated at
20 low temperatures or pressurized, or both, to make useful products
21 while allowing additives and contaminants to be removed. The
22 products of solvolysis include, but are not limited to, monomers,
23 intermediates, and valuable chemicals and raw materials. Solvolysis
24 includes, but is not limited to, the following:
25 (a) Hydrolysis.
26 (b) Aminolysis.
27 (c) Ammonolysis.
28 (d) Methanolysis.
