8 (ii) Discharge, by sewer or pipeline, to an off-site publicly
9 owned treatment works or other facility that is permitted under
10 part 31 or is otherwise approved by the department.
11 (iii) Discharge, by pumping and hauling, to an off-site publicly
12 owned treatment works or other facility that is permitted under
13 part 31 or is otherwise approved by the department.
14 (iv) Covered storage, as approved by the department, on-site
15 for not less than 180 days followed by land application under R
16 299.4111 of the MAC.
17 (10) (5) Beginning 2 years after the effective date of the
18 amendatory act that added this section, March 29, 2025, a person
19 shall not operate an innovative technology facility unless approved
20 by the department under a general permit, subject to subsections
21 (6) to (9).(11) and (14).
22 (11) (6) If the owner or operator of a materials utilization
23 facility in operation on the effective date of the amendatory act
24 that added this section March 29, 2023 is required to obtain
25 approval under a general permit under this act and submits a
26 complete application for approval by the deadline for obtaining
27 approval, the owner or operator is considered to be in compliance
28 with the approval requirement pending the department's approval or
29 denial of the application.
TMV H01604'25 (H-1) pmk8jn

21
1 (12) (7) An application for approval under a general permit
2 under this section shall be accompanied by a fee of $1,000.00. The
3 department shall approve or deny the application within 90 days
4 after receiving a complete permit application, the department shall
5 approve the application or shall deny the application and identify
6 with specificity the reason for the denial. If the application is
7 denied, within 6 months after the denial, the applicant may
8 resubmit the application together with additional information or
9 corrections necessary to address the reason for denial, without
10 paying an additional application fee.
11 (13) (8) The term of approval under a general permit under
12 this section is 5 years, except that the term of approval under an
13 innovative technology general permit is 2 years.
14 (14) (9) An approval under a general permit under this section
15 may be renewed upon the submittal of a timely and sufficient
16 application. To be considered timely and sufficient for purposes of
17 section 91 of the administrative procedures act of 1969, 1969 PA
18 306, MCL 24.291, an application for renewal of a general permit
19 approval shall meet both of the following requirements:
20 (a) Contain the information as required by the applicable
21 general permit application.
22 (b) Be received by the department not later than 90 days
23 before the expiration of the preceding authorization.
24 (15) (10) Fees collected under this subpart shall be deposited
25 in the perpetual care account established under section 11550.
26 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act does not take effect
27 unless House Bill No. 4257 of the 103rd Legislature is enacted into
28 law.
